Lenny's is a neighborhood pizzeria that does everything right:  Slices to go, with a special extra cheese + pepperoni slice for $3  Fresh baked pies ready in 15 minutes. They deliver using their own staff and are extremely quick.  Owner and staff are friendly and chatty if they start seeing you around.  Free order of zeppoles with a whole pie if they have some extra  Everything is very affordable - fries, wings, the non pizza stuff is great too.  Definitely stop by or consider ordering. It's not life changing pizza, but it's definitely very good and the overall experience has never been less than 5 stars.

It’s very hard to find a local pizzeria but Lennys HITS the spot... Personally I am a sauce guy and these guys have just the perfect mixture of both sauce and cheese.  They have a Wednesday Special that’s 2 pies for $19.99.. if you want extra toppings it’s just an extra $4 per pie.  Lennys is going to be our go to pizza joint for a classic nyc slice

Solid local pizzeria located on a busy road in Park Slope. There are only about 4 tables here, so most patrons should be looking to order for delivery or takeout.  The pizza oven perpetually heats up the interior, requiring large fans to run all the time to get some air circulation going.  The pizzas are generally what you expect from a traditional pizzeria. Don't expect to customize it with tofu or sun-dried tomatoes. They're not going to entertain it.  The pasta dishes were adequate. Not going to earn any awards, but the kids liked eating them just fine. Generous sauce and properly seasoned.

I hate leaving a poor review for a place that seems loved by so many. Like the old saying goes, "if you can't say something nice, don't say it at all". But it's the reviews that persuaded me to come here, so I feel obligated to throw in my two cents. I understand it's just a local pizzeria and I shouldn't expect much. However, we've been coming here once a week since January and each time we leave more disappointed. At first I thought maybe they were having an off night but each time it gets worse.  It's too bad because there's few options for pizza in the vicinity. The pizza is okay at best; the sauce is bland, the crust isn't crispy and there's too much cheese for me (but some people like a lot of cheese, so no points taken away for that). The worst part, and the reason I felt obligated to write this review, is the garlic knots are not just awful, they're inedible! They were so stale, I should have asked for my money back. They were obviously out all day and the staff should have known that. It may sound silly to leave a poor review for garlic knots, but if the garlic knots aren't fresh, what else is left out all day? The meat? The cheese? To end on a positive note, my son thinks their Grandma slice is good.

Lenny's has a good, solid, old school Brooklyn pie. They're not earth shatteringly good, but they're a reasonably priced place, and finding a decent pie in this neighborhood that isn't a super-expensive brick oven pie is tough.  Honestly I don't know if they'd be worth four stars in another neighborhood, but in Park Slope/ South Slope, you can't do much better for the price.

I was raised in Park Slope, about 7 blocks away from Lenny's. This was at a time when we had great pizza on every other block. A time when nothing but the finest ingredients were used to make a pie. So when I say that Lenny's was 7 blocks away, I sort of mean it might as well of been in another borough because there was no reason to travel that far for good pizza.  Except that Lenny's was that odd place that would be open on the weekends into the wee hours of the morning. So it became a destination after a night out with the old crew.  I recently stopped by to see that much had not changed, but the menu has gotten much larger. The grandma slice is a nod to a Neapolitan slice, but with a touch extra of Lenny's delicious sauce. I also had a white slice there recently that had this perfect fragrance of garlic with just the right blend of ricotta and mozzarella. Go get a slice when in the area, I think you'll be glad you did.
Lenny's makes delicious pizza that reminds me of the pizza I used to get as a kid. Real Italian sauce and a crust that's to die for! Try both the plain pie and pepperoni, you won't be disappointed.
